Durban - The funeral of a Phoenix father who died after his bike crashed into a tree is expected to take place on Tuesday. Nitesh Ramjith, 31, was killed when he allegedly lost control of his motorbike, a Honda CBR, crashed and into a palm tree in Rydalvale, Phoenix on Sunday morning. Head of Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) Prem Balram said he had sustained serious injuries. "A  private ambulance service was in attendance and the biker was stabilised on the scene. He was then transported to a hospital for further treatment.  The rear wheel of the Honda CBR separate on impact." He later died in hospital. Ramjith, who had two children aged 3 and 7,  will be cremated at the Clare Estate Hindu Crematorium. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed the incident. "Phoenix police are investigating a case of culpable homicide following the death of a 31-year-old man." Daily News